# PUBLIC / PRIVATE sync (required)

This workspace publishes **GitHub from `PUBLIC/`** only. **`PRIVATE/`** holds commercial and operational files.

## Where to edit

| Edit here (repo root) | Synced to |
|----------------------|-----------|
| App code, templates, static, `README.md`, `docs/`, `LICENSE`, `COMMERCIAL.md`, `gitpush.sh`, `tests/`, Docker files, public scripts | **`PUBLIC/`** |
| `firmgate-premium-licensing/`, `upload.sh`, `push.sh`, release ZIPs, local `.env`, `instance/` snapshots | **`PRIVATE/`** |
| `.solstak-backup.env` (Gitea password) | **repo root only** (gitignored; never in PUBLIC) |

**Do not** treat `PUBLIC/` or `PRIVATE/` as the source of truth for day-to-day edits. Change the **repo root** (or the private paths above), then sync.

## Required after changes

After **any** task that touches public-facing files (README, docs, screenshots, app UI, community edition, public scripts, etc.):

```bash
./sync.sh
```

After changes to **private** artifacts (license generator, `upload.sh`, release packages, etc.), ensure they live under the root paths listed above, then run:

```bash
./sync.sh
```

`./sync.sh` rebuilds **both** `PUBLIC/` and `PRIVATE/`. Always run it before telling the user to `gitpush`.

## Publishing

```bash
./gitpush.sh "commit message"   # runs sync, then commits/pushes PUBLIC/
./scripts/release-and-backup.sh # bump version, build ZIPs, push full backup to Gitea
```

Full workspace backup to [Gitea](https://git.solstak.com.au/): copy `.solstak-backup.env.example` → `.solstak-backup.env` and set `SOLSTAK_GIT_PASSWORD`. Runs automatically after `scripts/build_edition_packages.sh`.

Full file map: **`PRIVATE/AGENTS.md`** (never sync to PUBLIC).

## Never put in PUBLIC

`firmgate-premium-licensing/`, `upload.sh`, `push.sh`, `instance/`, `.env`, `dist/`, `PRIVATE/RELEASES/`, `.cursor/`, local secrets.
